Ask HN: What is my next best step?
text:
After nearly 4 years of being self taught, I am curious what my next best step is to pursue a career in technology.

My passion to get into the industry is at an extreme depth. I am well rounded in many aspects (more so a jack of all trades type [Full stack]) although I feel like I know nothing, which I hope is a normal feeling as there is unlimited knowledge to gain in the industry.

I have remained in an operations style position because I am able to work on small personal projects that make my job/life easier.

I have boosted and buffed my resume to the best of my ability (without flat out lying, lol) to say “I have quite a bit of experience”, while also saying I don’t have experience in certain aspects (teams, meetings, anything involved in a programming specific environment).

I have some good certificates I’ve grabbed just to show ability, I will soon begin to pursue a security cert or two as I have interest in the area. My major experience is in commercial sales, operations and service management.

I know there is more a could mention but would love to hear any available insight from industry professionals based on what I’ve provided.

Thanks, HN pals.
